OL,3,CRAF veteran, 88, says new life as
OL,4,Cfoster carer helps him 'stay young'
OL,6,F"I was an Air Cadet as a boy and had a
OL,7,Fmarvellous time doing that. I had a
OL,8,Fflying licence when I was still a
OL,9,Fschoolboy, long before I had a driving
OL,10,Flicence."I never intended to go into
OL,11,Fthe Air Force as a career," he added.
OL,13,F"I wanted to be a surgeon but had no
OL,14,Fchance of that as I couldn't afford
OL,15,Funiversity. I only joined the RAF for
OL,16,FNational Service.
